genresAdvancedInfo.name: guyanese pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre of popular music from Guyana, a country in South America. Guyanese pop features a fusion of Caribbean and South Asian musical influences, with elements of reggae, soca, and chutney music. The lyrics often touch on themes of love, social issues, and national pride. This genre has gained popularity in recent years, both within Guyana and among the diaspora community.
